 {"id":"frankenjax-x2v","title":"UBS: split JSON fixture parsing unwraps by risk","description":"Follow-up from frankenjax-gn6. UBS reports 41 serde_json::from_str(...).unwrap()/expect() warnings across tests, fixture readers, and conformance/parity helpers (examples include fj-conformance tests and fixture parsers). Classify fixture/test-only unwraps separately from runtime parsing, then convert reusable fixture readers to contextual Result errors so malformed fixtures fail with path/case context instead of raw panics.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T05:48:27.483893286Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T06:08:10.755463827Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T06:08:10.753299998Z","close_reason":"Converted reusable conformance oracle fixture JSON readers to contextual Result errors and removed raw parse panic sites from the touched fixture tests.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-x8f","title":"Remove fj-ad runtime tensor unwraps from AD linalg paths","description":"Follow-up from frankenjax-rdj unwrap/expect classification. Production-surface scan found 41 non-test unwrap/expect hits before cfg(test) in crates/fj-ad/src/lib.rs, concentrated in tensor/linalg AD rules: dims.last_mut().unwrap(), as_tensor().unwrap() chains around QR/SVD/eigh helpers, and primal_outs.into_iter().next().unwrap(). Replace with typed Result propagation or internal helper conversions that preserve current AD semantics and add focused regression tests for malformed/non-tensor paths.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T06:30:21.756087735Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T06:52:43.775978612Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T06:52:43.774036690Z","close_reason":"Completed: fj-ad linalg AD tensor-result unwraps and last-axis rewrites now return contextual AdError; added regression tests; full workspace check/clippy/test pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenjax-xfi","title":"UBS: clean FFI byte-conversion unwrap inventory","description":"Follow-up from frankenjax-gn6. UBS reports 28 try_into().unwrap()/expect() warnings, with sampled hits in fj-ffi tests and conformance FFI oracle byte conversions (for example crates/fj-ffi/src/call.rs and crates/fj-conformance/tests/ffi_oracle.rs). Introduce checked test helpers for fixed-width result byte decoding and replace direct try_into unwraps so conversion assumptions are explicit and failures carry context.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T05:48:22.893924794Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T05:56:51.637211690Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T05:56:51.635282896Z","close_reason":"Completed checked fixed-byte FFI result decoding helpers and removed direct try_into unwrap byte conversions.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"frankenjax-xjpu","title":"Harden BufferView slice range overflow","description":"Multi-pass bug hunt found crates/fj-runtime/src/buffer.rs BufferView::slice computes offset + len before validating bounds. For adversarial or saturated usize inputs this can panic in debug builds due integer overflow, and in optimized builds can wrap before the subsequent slice expression panics or misclassifies the range. Replace the addition with checked_add so out-of-range or overflowing slices return None as documented. Add a regression test using usize::MAX to prove BufferView::slice is panic-free and returns None for overflowing ranges. Validate with rch cargo test -p fj-runtime, rch cargo check -p fj-runtime --all-targets, rch cargo clippy -p fj-runtime --all-targets -- -D warnings, cargo fmt --check, and ubs on the touched file.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-28T20:28:47.354876805Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T20:28:47.584388428Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
